\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 33. A. moly} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 301 (1753). Bulb up to 2·5 cm in diameter, subglobose; outer tunic chartaceous. Stem 12-35 cm, terete. Leaves (1-)2(-3), 20-30 cm × 15-35 mm, almost basal, linear-lanceolate to lanceolate, glabrous, glaucous, keeled below. Spathe 2-valved, persistent, shorter than pedicels. Umbel 4-7 cm in diameter, fastigiate or hemispherical, many-flowered, without bulbils (var.{\i  moly}), rarely with bulbils and few flowers (var.{\i  bulbilliferum} Rouy); pedicels 15-35 mm, unequal, ascending. Perianth stellate; segments 9-12 × 4-5 mm, yellow, with greenish line outside, the outer elliptical, the inner oblanceolate, acute. Stamens shorter than segments; filaments 5-6 mm, yellow, simple. Ovary not prominently angled. Capsule covered by persistent, connivent perianth-segments. 2n = 14. {\i Shady mountain rocks. • E. Spain, S.W. France.} Ga Hs.
