\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 34. A. scorzonerifolium} Desf. ex DC. in Redouté, {\i Liliacées}{\b  2}: t. 99 (1804). Bulb c. 1·5 cm in diameter, subglobose; outer tunics papery. Stem 14-30 cm, angled above. Leaves 1-3, 18-40 cm × 3-7 mm, almost basal, linear, keeled below, glaucous. Spathe 1-valved, caducous. Umbel 4-5 cm in diameter, fastigiate, with up to 15 flowers and without bulbils (var. {\i xericiense} (Pérez Lara) R. Fernandes), or with bulbils and few flowers (var.{\i  scorzonerifolium}); pedicels 15-30 mm, ascending. Perianth stellate; segments 7-10 × 2-4 mm, yellow, lanceolate or narrowly elliptical, acute or obtuse. Stamens shorter than segments; filaments 4-6 mm, yellow, simple. Ovary distinctly angled, with 6 minute crests. 2n = 14.{\i  Rock crevices. • W. & C. Spain, N.W. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
