\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 35. A. triquetrum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 300 (1753). Bulbs 1·5 cm in diameter; outer tunic membranous. Stem 10-45 cm. Leaves usually 2-3, up to 42 cm × 17 mm. Spathe up to 2·5 cm. Umbel with 3-15 flowers, usually one-sided, lax, without bulbils; pedicels up to 25 mm. Perianth drooping, campanulate; segments 10-18 × 2-5 mm, white, with distinct longitudinal green stripe, lanceolate, acute. Stamens 6-7 mm. Capsule 6-7 mm. 2n = 18.{\i  Woods, streamsides and damp, shady places. W. Mediterranean region.} Bl Co Ga Hs It Sa Si [Az Br Hb *Lu].
