\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 36. A. pendulinum} Ten., {\i Prodr. Fl. Nap.} 22 (1810). Bulbs c. 1 cm in diameter; outer tunic membranous. Stem 6-25 cm. Leaves 2, up to 25 cm × 7 mm, soon withering. Umbel with 5-9 flowers, lax, not secund, without bulbils; pedicels up to 40 mm, ascending at anthesis, later drooping. Perianth stellate; segments 3-5 × 1·1-1·4 mm, white, with longitudinal green stripe, lanceolate, acute. Filaments 4·5 mm. Capsule 4-6 mm. 2n = 14. {\i Woods and damp, shady places. • C. Mediterranean region.} Co It Sa Si.
